"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-houston-cougars-social-posts-uh-carl-lewis-ushers-in-opening-ceremony-of-the-2024-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Carl Lewis has no problem maintaining his balance on land.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 58, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The nine-time Olympic champion and the IOC\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sportsman of the 20th century, has faced numerous foes throughout his illustrious career.\", \"from\": 59, \"to\": 195, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, at the opening ceremony for the Paris Games on Friday, he encountered a new challenge: a rocking boat.\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 307, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis joined fellow gold medalists Serena Williams, Rafael Nadal, and Nadia Com\\u00c4\\u0083neci on a boat cruising down the Seine, carrying the Olympic flame to the traditional cauldron lighting ceremony.\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 361, \"end\": 373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Boulanger\", \"score\": 0.9959924082484335, \"rank\": 0.0033314667449616084, \"text\": \"Nadia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Boulanger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Boulanger\"}, {\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999281109156041, \"rank\": 7.189362398473122e-05, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What was anticipated to be a grand and symbolic journey quickly turned into a tense and precarious situation.\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The boat ride, which seemed almost as prolonged and intense as Nadal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s legendary five-setter against Roger Federer in the 2008 Wimbledon final, proved difficult for the athletes.\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 718, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roger Federer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The strong headwinds caused concern that the flame might blow out, visibly worrying Nadal.\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 881, \"end\": 886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 0.9999999994465725, \"rank\": 5.533217942391758e-10, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams and Lewis were alarmed at the thought of balancing a naked flame in one hand while maintaining their stability with the other.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 1023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 901, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"score\": 0.9532557750374233, \"rank\": 0.04903639315482601, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Com\\u00c4\\u0083neci, drawing on her balance beam experience from her two Olympic golds, appeared the least troubled by the boat\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s movements.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At one point, Williams, clearly distressed, sought reassurance by holding onto Com\\u00c4\\u0083neci.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"@Carl_Lewis, nine-time Olympic champion and coach of@UHCougarTF, proudly helped usher in the Olympic flame at today\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s opening ceremony of the 2024 Paris Olympics!#OlympiansMadeHerepic.twitter.com/mu3a8WkSae  Lewis\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 illustrious Olympic career is well-documented.\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 1984 Los Angeles Games, he achieved a historic feat, matching Jesse Owens\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 1936 record by winning four gold medals in the 100m, 200m, long jump, and 4x100m relay.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His talent was complemented by his remarkable longevity in the sport.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 1988 Olympics, he secured gold in the 100 meters and the long jump.\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He continued his winning streak in 1992, claiming gold in the long jump and anchoring the U.S. 4x100m relay team to a world record time of 37.40 seconds.\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2024 Paris Olympics: How to Watch former and current Houston Cougars in events  This eventful boat ride captured the unpredictable nature of live events.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2040, \"end\": 2047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"score\": 0.9778280236064257, \"rank\": 0.01837132498372706, \"text\": \"Houston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the discomfort and anxiety, Lewis and his fellow athletes persevered, showcasing the resilience and adaptability that have defined their careers.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"score\": 0.9532557750374233, \"rank\": 0.04903639315482601, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis, now in his ninth year as Houston's Track and Field coach, continues to inspire new generations of athletes with his enduring legacy and commitment to the sport.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2327, \"end\": 2334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"score\": 0.9778280236064257, \"rank\": 0.01837132498372706, \"text\": \"Houston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony's moment on the Seine will be remembered as a testament to the spirit of the Olympics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a blend of celebration, challenge, and the unwavering determination of its champions.\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2501, \"end\": 2506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.99992811